JWST Mission Operations Viz Pack
=================================

Themed Canvas 2D custom visualizations for James Webb Space Telescope
mission operations dashboards. Deep space aesthetic with infrared
spectrum palette and hexagonal motifs.

Visualizations
--------------

jwst_heat_grid          Hexagonal heat grid for sensor temperature monitoring
jwst_instrument_matrix  2x2 instrument status cards with drilldown
jwst_data_cascade       Animated data download cascade with particle effects
jwst_observation_queue  Prioritized observation target list
jwst_power_horizon      Dual-layer area chart (solar gen vs consumption)
jwst_kpi_tile           Single value KPI with sparkline and threshold colors

Design Tokens
-------------

Font display:   Oxanium (base64-embedded)
Font mono:      JetBrains Mono (base64-embedded)
Dark bg:        #06080F (void black)
Gold accent:    #D4A537 (JWST mirror gold)
Cyan:           #00B4D8 (infrared short wavelength)
Magenta:        #E040A0 (infrared mid wavelength)

Data Sources
------------

All demo data via CSV lookups in lookups/ directory:

sensor_temperatures.csv   6 sensors x 24 hours = 144 rows
instrument_status.csv     4 instruments
data_downloads.csv        5 data bands
observation_queue.csv     5 observation targets
power_balance.csv         48 time points (30min intervals)
kpi_summary.csv           6 key metrics with sparkline data

Dashboard JSON Options
----------------------

Every custom viz panel MUST have:
  "backgroundColor": "transparent"

Viz type format:
  "type": "jwst_viz_pack.{viz_name}"

Building
--------

Prerequisites: Node.js (for webpack)

  chmod +x build.sh
  ./build.sh

The script builds all 6 vizs, verifies AMD wrappers, and creates
dist/jwst_viz_pack.tar.gz for Splunk installation.

Hero Image
----------

Place a JWST deep field image at:
  appserver/static/images/hero_jwst.jpg

Recommended: NASA public domain imagery from images.nasa.gov
Search for "Webb deep field" or "Pillars of Creation Webb"
